ping ftp por simbolo de sistema y tambien ssh
accedemos desde navegador para confirmar http

========================================================================
# Bloquear ICMP (Ping)
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-rich-rule='rule protocol value="icmp" drop'

# Bloquear SSH (Puerto 22)
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --remove-service=ssh
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=22/tcp --reject

# Bloquear HTTP (Puerto 80)
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --remove-service=http
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=80/tcp --reject

# Aplicar cambios
sudo firewall-cmd --reload
=====
Ver errores del último dnf update
sudo dnf update -y 2>&1 | tee /tmp/dnf_update.log

Verificar que EPEL está activo
dnf repolist | grep epel

Reinstalar EPEL si falla
sudo dnf remove epel-release -y && sudo dnf install https://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/epel-release-latest-9.noarch.rpm -y

Limpiar caché de dnf y reintentar
sudo dnf clean all && sudo dnf makecache

Habilitar CRB (alternativa a subscription-manager )
sudo dnf config-manager --set-enabled crb

En Rocky Linux 9, usar crb en lugar de codeready-builder-for-rhel-9
Verificar archivo ldconfig
cat /etc/ld.so.conf.d/local.conf && sudo ldconfig -v 2>&1 | head -20

Error: "FATAL: No DAQ modules available"
ldconfig -p | grep daq && pkg-config --modversion libdaq

Error: "Could not open interface ens160"
ip link show && sudo ip link set dev ens160 up

Error: "snort: command not found"
ls /usr/local/snort/bin/snort && sudo ln -sf /usr/local/snort/bin/snort /usr/bin/snort

Error de librería compartida al ejecutar snort
ldd /usr/local/snort/bin/snort | grep "not found" && sudo ldconfig

Error: "Permission denied" al capturar paquetes
sudo setcap cap_net_raw,cap_net_admin=eip /usr/local/snort/bin/snort

Ver log de sistema por errores de snort
sudo journalctl -xe | grep -i snort | tail -30
